ENTRY       EC 2.7.4.26                 Enzyme
NAME        isopentenyl phosphate kinase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring phosphorus-containing groups;
            Phosphotransferases with a phosphate group as acceptor
SYSNAME     ATP:isopentenyl phosphate phosphotransferase
REACTION    ATP + isopentenyl phosphate = ADP + isopentenyl diphosphate [RN:R10093]
ALL_REAC    R10093
SUBSTRATE   ATP [CPD:C00002];
            isopentenyl phosphate [CPD:C20345]
PRODUCT     ADP [CPD:C00008];
            isopentenyl diphosphate [CPD:C00129]
COMMENT     The enzyme is involved in the mevalonate pathway in Archaea [1]. The activity has also been identified in the plant Mentha piperita (peppermint) [2]. It is strictly specific for ATP but can use other phosphate acceptors such as dimethylallyl phosphate, geranyl phosphate, or fosfomycin.
